# Supabase Integration Implementation Plan

This plan outlines the steps to connect your conciergerie frontend application to the Supabase database, replacing the mock data with real backend functionality.

## Overview

Your frontend is well-structured with:
- ✅ Complete UI components for all entities
- ✅ React Router navigation setup
- ✅ Centralized state management via [useAppState](file:///c:/Users/dry-_/OneDrive/Bureau/Apios/conciergerie/src/hooks/useAppState.tsx#202-209)
- ✅ Complete database schema with RLS policies
- ✅ Supabase environment variables configured

**Goal**: Replace the mock data layer with Supabase services while maintaining the same component interfaces.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Database Improvements**: I have updated the plan to include industry standards and Supabase best practices:
> 1. **Auth Triggers**: Automatically create a profile when a user signs up.
> 2. **Recursive RLS Fix**: Using a secure function `is_admin()` to avoid recursion and improve performance.
> 3. **Profiles naming**: Standardizing on the `profiles` table name throughout the schema.
> 4. **Encapsulated Security**: Using specific functions for role-based access control.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Database Schema Application**: Please confirm if you want me to apply these improvements directly to your [database-schema.sql](file:///c:/Users/dry-_/OneDrive/Bureau/Apios/conciergerie/src/docs/database-schema.sql) file.

